This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump during a Hanukkah celebration at the White House. In his speech, the President thanked Vice President Pence, Secretary Mnuchin, Secretary Shulkin, and First Lady Melania for their support. He also acknowledged the presence of his grandchildren and spoke about the significance of the Hanukkah story and the resilience of the Jewish people. The President expressed gratitude for Jewish congregations in the United States and emphasized the enduring bond between America and Israel. He highlighted the historical significance of two Hanukkah lamps present at the event and honored a Holocaust survivor in attendance. The President concluded by wishing everyone a blessed and happy Hanukkah.